verses.roman:
atyanta-nigūḍha ei rasera siddhānta
svarūpa-gosāñi mātra jānena ekānta

synonyms: atyanta—extremely; nigūḍha—deep; ei—this; rasera—of mellow; siddhānta—conclusion; svarūpa-gosāñi—Svarūpa Dāmodara Gosvāmī; mātra—only; jānena—knows; ekānta—much.
translation: This conclusion of rasa is extremely deep. Only Svarūpa Dāmodara knows much about it.
